media.altText: [snapshot] I am sorry for people's experiences with bad bosses. There are so many reasons why a boss is bad - they can be abusive, harassing (at the extreme end) or oblivious to overwork and the need to treat people as human beings, acknowledging their non-work life is important too. Bosses are people too, and in working with many organizations I have discovered that bosses are often stressed or burned out. Often times people step into these roles and they are not fully prepared to be leaders, and with some good training they can be better people and better managers. But some bosses get into their jobs because they are narcissists and they want power, and in many companies these people have been rewarded and protected at the same time these companies lose good staff. Healthy work definitely requires good managers, support from supervisors is a fundamental principle for all organizations and individuals.
